“My administration has a great commitment to the Mexican people to reduce violence,” Mr. Pe<0xC3><0xB1>a Nieto explained earlier this week to U.S. President Barack Obama in the Oval Office.
“I’m going to propose a new security strategy that will allow us to achieve that goal.”
Before he rubbed shoulders with the U.S. president, Mr. Pe<0xC3><0xB1>a’s previous political experience was as governor of his home state of Mexico.
A heavily populated and rapidly growing state, it surrounds the capital; opinions about the new leader are divided on this territory in which he used to move.
A sincere man
In the bucolic city of Valle del Bravo, for example, he is fondly remembered.
