More than 1,000 women were killed in the state of Mexico while Mr. Pe<0xC3><0xB1>a Nieto was governor, a much higher rate than that of Ciudad Juarez, unfortunately famous for its violence and a place that is synonymous with the murder of innocent women.
Mr. Pe<0xC3><0xB1>a Nieto’s critics say, at best, that he failed to address the problem of femicide while in office.
